hopobject.body: Which year are you in? bystrictin gnc There has been friction with the Coalition over Threadneedle Street's demands that banks should raise their capital levels. The former governor, Lord King, complained that the Treasury and Downing Street put pressure on the Bank to water down its demands. The Business Secretary, Vince Cable, this week echoed the complaints of bankers that the Bank was acting like a "capital Taliban".
